In remarks made on August 1, 2019, President Trump addressed questions about the tariffs imposed on China and the recent drop in the stock market. He stated that he is not concerned about the market's reaction and that he expected it due to people's lack of understanding about the situation. He reiterated that the tariffs on China are necessary because China has been taking hundreds of billions of dollars out of the United States for years. He also mentioned that companies are moving out of China, which is causing China's economy to suffer. President Trump expressed his belief that China wants to make a deal but has not been moving fast enough. He also mentioned the ongoing protests in Hong Kong, stating that it is a matter between Hong Kong and China. The President also discussed his intention to impose tariffs on Mexico, the issue of North Korea's missile launches, and his views on Democratic candidates and the Russia investigation.